glew
------------------------------------------
The OpenGL Extension Wrangler Library (GLEW) is a cross-platform 
open-source C/C++ extension loading library. GLEW provides efficient 
run-time mechanisms for determining which OpenGL extensions are 
supported on the target platform. OpenGL core and extension 
functionality is exposed in a single header file.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.7-1
  libGL1-7.8.2-1
  libGLU1-7.8.2-1
  libX11_6-1.3.5-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.20.51-2
  cygport-0.10.0-1
  gcc4-core-4.5.0-1
  make-3.81-2
  sed-4.2.1-1

Canonical website:
  http://glew.sourceforge.net/

Canonical download:
  http://downloads.sourceforge.net/glew/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack glew-1.5.6-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./glew-1.5.6-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/glew-1.5.6-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/glew-1.5.6-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libGLEW-devel-1.5.6-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libGLEW1.5-1.5.6-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

